  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">HAI through the establishment of a youth-led musical choir aims to reduce tensions among the Syrian refugees and affected vulnerable Lebanese communities in Akkar, using music as a tool to promote and advocate for tolerance and peace. 35 adolescent boys and girls from Syrian and Lebanese communities established a choir within which they can safely dream and create lasting friendships, discover new talents and gain specialized skills, and become role-models for other youths in their communities.</narrative>
